Over 9 million children ages 5–11 years have received at least one dose of #COVID19 vaccine.

Your participation in v-safe helps CDC monitor the safety of COVID-19 vaccines for everyone.
 
Learn more: https://t.co/S4ZmF2foa9. https://t.co/fFWJC29XuL
#HCPs: Improving childhood vaccination rates is a collective effort. Learn how HCPs can work together to improve rates: https://t.co/y8gykrKeYx. https://t.co/a4hcKmR5yn

New @CDCMMWR found that for the second year, #COVID19 was third leading cause of death in US in 2021, after heart disease & cancer. 

Stay up to date on your COVID-19 vaccines to help prevent serious illness and death. Learn more: https://t.co/WKQpZOueVQ. https://t.co/O6gowonFmX

If you’re eligible for a #COVID19 booster and haven’t received one, make a plan to get one now.

Everyone ages 12 years and older should get a booster when it’s time.

Find one near you: https://t.co/2akIUZ14Rd. https://t.co/eM1aACqqxh

The latest MMWR Weekly #COVID19 Briefing is live. This episode covers 3 reports, including reports highlighting COVID-19 mortality & vaccine coverage in Hong Kong, Omicron infections in people previously infected w/ Delta and more. Listen & subscribe: https://t.co/I9Zs1YquaF. https://t.co/GYPBWgtJtd

Over 9 million children ages 5–11 years have received at least one dose of #COVID19 vaccine.

Enroll in v-safe so you can quickly and easily share with CDC how your child feels after getting a COVID-19 vaccine.

Learn more: https://t.co/S4ZmF2foa9. https://t.co/JW2RQIxDdm

Are you up to date on your #COVID19 vaccines?
You’re up to date on COVID-19 vaccines when you’ve received all vaccines recommended for you, including additional doses and boosters when you’re eligible.
Learn more: https://t.co/009bOerScg. https://t.co/CgpsD6B96c

#HCPs: The ACIP has new recommendations on Hepatitis B, Pneumococcal & Zoster vaccines. This Current Issues in Immunizations recording now available at https://t.co/lmghb6s6pC. https://t.co/QEJ6NgnYDN

Why should you stay up to date with your #COVID19 vaccines?

Staying up to date with your COVID-19 vaccines lowers your risk of getting seriously ill, being hospitalized, or dying from COVID-19.

Find your vaccine or booster: https://t.co/xbvNibdkCt.
#HCPs: Some of your littlest patients might have missed their routine vaccinations. Talk to their parents about getting them caught up. https://t.co/kAaLqImzUt #VaccinesWork https://t.co/4aHtrS6GYM
